99\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ymz1665703119661.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ymz1665703119661.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ymz1665703119661.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ymz1665703119661\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Implementation Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Type of component implementation.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__section_xtz_tj1_dxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d299338e51\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__p_d110939e1_d110940e1_d110941e1\">Select an implementation from the list of available\n        types.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__p_d110942e1_d110943e1_d110944e1\">A component cannot have both Uniface and operating\n        system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating\n        system implementation can also have one or more of the non-Uniface implementations shown in\n        the list.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__note_c25_vj1_dxb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You cannot create a Uniface implementation if the\n        component name exceeds 16 bytes.</div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Component Implementations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\">Implementation type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\">Operations available by default</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\">Editable</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\">Comments</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"2\"> Uniface Component </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> Y </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> These are built-in Uniface operations. You can\n                     define parameters for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code> operation only. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> These are explicit operations. If you define\n                     operations named <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>  they are\n                     activated implicitly. For more information on <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code>  and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code> see <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">operation</span>. <p class=\"p\">You cannot\n                        define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\"> C </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\">You can define the default operations\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code> , <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code> , and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                     and the implicit operations <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.\n                        <p class=\"p\">You cannot define parameters for <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>,\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">INIT</code> or\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">CLEANUP</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">EXEC</code>\n                        parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation,\n                        these parameters remain available for the C implementation.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\"> COM </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\"> Java Call-in </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\"> Stored Procedure </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\"> None </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> No default operations are available. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__1\"> Operating System Service </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMAND</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMANDOUT</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__3\"> N </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ymz1665703119661__table_d13007e1_d13008e1_d13009e1__entry__4\"> Enter operating system commands using\n\t\t\t\t ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to\n\t\t\t\t redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. <p class=\"p\">The maximum length of a command is 511\n\t\t\t\t bytes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__section_nlc_nk1_dxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d299338e301\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__ul_xtd_4k1_dxb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ymz1665703119661__li_d3116e1_d3117e1_d3118e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnm1665702714020.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnm1665702714020.html\" title=\"A Signature Implementation is a Development Object that defines the technology used to implement a signature, such as Uniface, COM, SOAP and so on. A Signature can have multiple implementations. Each Signature Implementation captures the technology-specific properties of the Signature, Signature Operation, and Signature Parameters.\">Signature Implementation</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3617199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Implementation Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Implementation Type Type of component implementation. Description Select an implementation from the list of available types. A component cannot have both Uniface and operating system implementations at the same time. However, a component with a Uniface or operating system implementation can also have one or more of the non-Uniface implementations shown in the list. Note: You cannot create a Uniface implementation if the component name exceeds 16 bytes. Table 1. Component Implementations Implementation type Operations available by default Editable Comments Uniface Component ACCEPT , EXEC , QUIT Y These are built-in Uniface operations. You can define parameters for the EXEC operation only. INIT , CLEANUP These are explicit operations. If you define operations named INIT and CLEANUP they are activated implicitly. For more information on INIT and CLEANUP see operation . You cannot define parameters for INIT and CLEANUP . C None N You can define the default operations ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC and the implicit operations INIT and CLEANUP . You cannot define parameters for ACCEPT , QUIT , INIT or CLEANUP . However, if you define both 4GL and C implementations for a component, the ACCEPT , QUIT , and EXEC parameters become available. If you then delete the 4GL implementation, these parameters remain available for the C implementation. COM None N No default operations are available. Java Call-in None N No default operations are available. Stored Procedure None N No default operations are available. Operating System Service COMMAND , COMMANDOUT N Enter operating system commands using ProcScript to be executed via an Operating System Service. You can use your assignment file to redirect the Operating System Service components to a Uniface server. The maximum length of a command is 511 bytes. Applies To Signature Implementation Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}